{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> εὐσταθ-έω</b>, <br /> <b>to be steady, stable</b>, ὅταν πολίταις εὐσταθῶσι δαίμονες <b>are favourable</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Rhesus” 317; εὐ. ταῖς διανοίαις 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 6.51 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εὐστάθει <b>rest in peace</b>! in an epitaph, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 14.1464\">Refs</a>]; <b>to be calm, tranquil</b>, of the sea, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “VH” 1.30; οὐκ εὐ. οἱ ὄρνιθες 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.281b. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>enjoy sound, stable health</b>, εὐ. καὶ ὑγιαίνειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 68, compare 413, 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 1.87, 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] <i>middle</i> cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Oribasius Medicus 7.8.1. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> of cities or countries, <b>enjoy tranquillity</b>, εὐσταθοῦσα βασιλεία [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “OGI” 56.19 (Canopus, 1st c.BC: Ptolemaeus Epigrammaticus III)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; τὴν πόλιν εὐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 708.37 (Istropolis, 2nd c.BC),compare 2nd c.AD: Appianus Historicus “Ἰβηρική” 9. \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G7567","accentedUnicode":"εὐσταθέω","shortDef":"be stable","mediumDef":"be stable","stepGloss":"be stable","stepTransliteration":"eustatheō","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}